Cases in various countries:
Americas
---
- Americas. 30 Oct 2021. The Pan American Health Organization (PAHO) reports 122 203 chikungunya cases year to date [2021] in the Americas. This compares with 103 000 total cases reported in all of 2020. Brazil accounted for more than 97% of the total with 119 019 cases, including 57 221 confirmed cases. This is followed by Guatemala with 1091 cases and Belize with 737. In the region, 8 fatalities were reported, all in Brazil (http://outbreaknewstoday.com/chikungunya-in-the-americas-more-than-120k-cases-reported-97-in-brazil-59705/).

[Maps showing the location of the affected islands and countries mentioned below can be accessed at
https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8699610,35574;
